                <h1>Stalin: The Controversial Legacy of a Soviet Leader</h1>
                <p>Joseph Stalin was a prominent Soviet leader who ruled from the mid-1920s until his death in 1953. Known for his totalitarian regime, Stalin implemented vast industrialization and collectivization efforts that transformed the Soviet Union but led to millions of deaths. He played a key role in World War II but left a legacy marked by repression and human rights abuses.</p>
